race.comment: Pike stays aboard SETAGAYA (11), and that's a decent push for the mare's chances. She won a Lark Hill trial and jumped a $3.2 favourite at Albany first up but had no luck from a wide gate. Draws awkwardly again but will appreciate the longer sprint and she flies second-up. ELVIRA STAR (7) won her Maiden here off a longish break and then spiked her figures beaten 2L at Ascot in tougher than this. Carries more weight but presents fitter and draws for a soft run. ANTZ PANTZ BABY (3) improved here in a similar contest and has more to offer. She's in the mix. HIGHLY SPOKEN (2) looked a run short here first-up and will appreciate the step up in trip. He will be around the mark.
